# Frontend Design Guidelines

Professional design principles for building beautiful, usable interfaces.

## Mobile-First Philosophy

**Design for mobile first, then enhance for larger screens.** Most users are on mobile devices—treat desktop as the progressive enhancement, not the other way around.

### Why Mobile-First

- Forces focus on essential content and actions
- Ensures touch-friendly interactions work everywhere
- Prevents "desktop afterthought" mobile experiences
- Easier to add than to remove complexity

### Mobile-First Rules

1. **Start every design at 320-375px width** before considering larger screens
2. **Touch targets minimum 44x44px**—thumbs are imprecise
3. **Bottom navigation > hamburger menus**—reachable with one hand
4. **Full-width buttons on mobile**—easier to tap
5. **Avoid hover-dependent interactions**—touch has no hover state
6. **Test on real devices**—emulators miss performance and touch issues
7. **Consider thumb zones**—primary actions in bottom 2/3 of screen

### Mobile-Specific Patterns

```tsx
// ✅ Bottom sheet instead of modal (more natural on mobile)
<Sheet>
  <SheetTrigger>Open</SheetTrigger>
  <SheetContent side="bottom">
    {/* Content slides up from bottom */}
  </SheetContent>
</Sheet>

// ✅ Sticky bottom action bar
<div className="fixed bottom-0 inset-x-0 p-4 bg-background border-t">
  <Button className="w-full">Primary Action</Button>
</div>

// ✅ Mobile-first responsive classes
<div className="px-4 md:px-6 lg:px-8">           {/* Padding scales up */}
<div className="text-base md:text-lg">           {/* Font scales up */}
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2"> {/* Stack → Grid */}
```

### Mobile Touch Considerations

| Element | Minimum Size | Recommended |
|---------|--------------|-------------|
| Buttons | 44x44px | 48x48px |
| List items | 44px height | 48-56px height |
| Icon buttons | 44x44px | 48x48px |
| Spacing between targets | 8px | 12px |

### Mobile Performance

- Lazy load images and heavy components
- Minimize JavaScript bundle size
- Use skeleton screens over spinners (feels faster)
- Avoid layout shifts—reserve space for async content
- Test on throttled 3G connections

## Core Principles

### Visual Hierarchy

Establish clear importance levels:

```
1. Primary action → Bold, high-contrast, prominent placement
2. Secondary content → Medium weight, supporting position
3. Tertiary info → Subtle, smaller, muted colors
```

**Rules:**
- One primary action per screen/section (avoid competing CTAs)
- Size, color, and whitespace all communicate importance
- Users should know where to look within 3 seconds

### Spacing System

Use a consistent spacing scale (e.g., 4px base):

```
4px  → Tight: icon-to-label, inline elements
8px  → Compact: related items, form field gaps
16px → Default: between components, card padding
24px → Relaxed: section separation
32px → Loose: major section breaks
48px+ → Generous: page-level separation
```

**Rules:**
- Related items = less space between them
- Unrelated items = more space between them
- Padding inside containers > gaps between containers
- Increase spacing on larger screens

### Typography

**Font sizes (mobile-first):**
```
12px → Captions, labels, metadata
14px → Body text, UI elements
16px → Default body, inputs
18-20px → Lead text, important body
24-32px → Section headings
36-48px → Page titles
```

**Rules:**
- Maximum 2-3 font weights per page (regular, medium, bold)
- Line height: 1.4-1.6 for body text, 1.2-1.3 for headings
- Maximum line length: 65-75 characters for readability
- Left-align body text (avoid justified text on web)

### Color

**Semantic colors:**
```
Primary   → Brand actions, key interactive elements
Secondary → Supporting actions, less prominent UI
Success   → Confirmations, completed states (green)
Warning   → Caution, non-blocking issues (amber/yellow)
Error     → Failures, destructive actions (red)
Neutral   → Backgrounds, borders, disabled states
```

**Rules:**
- Maintain 4.5:1 contrast ratio for text (WCAG AA)
- Don't rely on color alone—use icons, text, or patterns too
- Limit palette: 1 primary, 1-2 accents, plus neutrals
- Test in both light and dark modes

## Component Patterns

### Buttons

```tsx
// ✅ Clear hierarchy
<Button variant="default">Save Changes</Button>     // Primary
<Button variant="secondary">Cancel</Button>         // Secondary
<Button variant="ghost">Learn more</Button>         // Tertiary

// ✅ Good button text
"Save Changes" | "Create Account" | "Send Message"

// ❌ Vague button text
"Submit" | "Click Here" | "OK" | "Yes"
```

**Rules:**
- Minimum touch target: 44x44px (mobile)
- Button text = verb + noun ("Create Project", not "Create")
- Destructive actions require confirmation or undo
- Loading states: disable + show spinner + change text ("Saving...")

### Forms

```tsx
// ✅ Good form structure
<form>
  <div className="space-y-4">
    <div>
      <Label htmlFor="email">Email address</Label>
      <Input id="email" type="email" placeholder="you@example.com" />
      <p className="text-sm text-muted-foreground mt-1">
        We'll never share your email.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</form>
```

**Rules:**
- Labels above inputs (not floating labels for complex forms)
- Mark optional fields, not required (most fields should be required)
- Show validation errors inline, below the field
- Use appropriate input types (email, tel, number, date)
- Single-column layouts convert better than multi-column
- Submit button at bottom, aligned left or full-width on mobile

### Empty States

Never show blank screens. Empty states should:
1. Explain what will appear here
2. Guide users to take action
3. Feel intentional, not broken

```tsx
// ✅ Helpful empty state
<div className="text-center py-12">
  <FolderIcon className="mx-auto h-12 w-12 text-muted-foreground" />
  <h3 className="mt-4 text-lg font-medium">No projects yet</h3>
  <p className="mt-2 text-muted-foreground">
    Get started by creating your first project.
  </p>
  <Button className="mt-6">Create Project</Button>
</div>
```

### Loading States

```tsx
// ✅ Skeleton screens (preferred for known layouts)
<div className="space-y-4">
  <Skeleton className="h-8 w-48" />
  <Skeleton className="h-4 w-full" />
  <Skeleton className="h-4 w-3/4" />
</div>

// ✅ Spinners (for unknown content or quick loads)
<Loader2 className="h-6 w-6 animate-spin" />
```

**Rules:**
- Show skeleton for loads >200ms
- Match skeleton shapes to actual content
- Avoid layout shift when content loads
- Never block the entire screen if only part is loading

### Error States

```tsx
// ✅ Inline field error
<div>
  <Input className="border-destructive" />
  <p className="text-sm text-destructive mt-1">
    Please enter a valid email address
  </p>
</div>

// ✅ Page-level error with recovery
<Alert variant="destructive">
  <AlertTitle>Unable to load data</AlertTitle>
  <AlertDescription>
    Please check your connection and try again.
  </AlertDescription>
  <Button variant="outline" size="sm" className="mt-2">
    Retry
  </Button>
</Alert>
```

**Rules:**
- Be specific: "Email is invalid" not "Error"
- Offer recovery actions when possible
- Preserve user input on errors
- Don't use red for non-error states

## Layout Patterns

### Responsive Design

**Always write mobile styles first, then add breakpoint overrides:**

```tsx
// ✅ Mobile-first: base styles are mobile, breakpoints add desktop
<div className="
  flex flex-col        // Mobile: stack vertically
  md:flex-row          // Desktop: row layout
  gap-4               
  md:gap-6             // Desktop: more spacing
  p-4
  md:p-8               // Desktop: more padding
">

// ❌ Desktop-first: harder to maintain, mobile as afterthought
<div className="flex-row md:flex-col p-8 md:p-4">
```

**Breakpoints (use sparingly):**
```
sm: 640px  → Large phones (rarely needed)
md: 768px  → Tablets (primary breakpoint)
lg: 1024px → Small laptops
xl: 1280px → Desktops (use for wide layouts)
```

**Responsive Patterns:**

| Mobile | Desktop |
|--------|---------|
| Bottom navigation | Sidebar or top nav |
| Single column | Multi-column grid |
| Full-width buttons | Inline/auto-width buttons |
| Bottom sheets | Modals/dialogs |
| Stacked cards | Card grid |
| Collapsed menus | Expanded navigation |

**Rules:**
- Base styles = mobile styles (no breakpoint prefix)
- Only add breakpoints when layout genuinely needs to change
- Navigation: bottom bar (mobile) → sidebar or top nav (desktop)
- Cards: stack vertically (mobile) → grid (desktop)
- Content width: max-w-prose for text, max-w-screen-xl for app UI
- Test at 320px, 375px, 768px, and 1280px minimum

### Whitespace

Whitespace is not empty space—it's a design element:

- **Micro whitespace:** padding inside components
- **Macro whitespace:** margins between sections

**Rules:**
- More whitespace = more premium feel
- Dense UIs feel complex; spacious UIs feel simple
- Don't fill every pixel—let content breathe
- Increase whitespace as screen size increases

### Cards & Containers

```tsx
// ✅ Consistent card styling
<Card className="p-6">
  <CardHeader className="pb-4">
    <CardTitle>Title</CardTitle>
    <CardDescription>Supporting text</CardDescription>
  </CardHeader>
  <CardContent>
    {/* Content */}
  </CardContent>
</Card>
```

**Rules:**
- Consistent border-radius across the app (4px, 8px, or 12px)
- Subtle shadows for elevation, not harsh drop shadows
- Border OR shadow, rarely both
- Group related content in cards

## Interaction Design

### Feedback & Microinteractions

Every action should have feedback:

```tsx
// ✅ Button with loading state
<Button disabled={isPending}>
  {isPending && <Loader2 className="mr-2 h-4 w-4 animate-spin" />}
  {isPending ? 'Saving...' : 'Save'}
</Button>

// ✅ Toast for async confirmations
toast.success('Changes saved')
toast.error('Failed to save changes')
```

**Rules:**
- Immediate feedback: hover, focus, active states
- Progress feedback: loading spinners, progress bars
- Completion feedback: success toasts, checkmarks
- Transitions: 150-300ms for UI, 300-500ms for modals

### Hover & Focus States

```tsx
// ✅ Clear interactive affordance
<button className="
  hover:bg-accent 
  focus-visible:outline-none 
  focus-visible:ring-2 
  focus-visible:ring-ring
  transition-colors
">
  Click me
</button>
```

**Rules:**
- All interactive elements need hover AND focus states
- Focus rings for keyboard navigation (accessibility)
- Cursor changes: pointer for buttons/links, text for inputs
- Disable hover effects on touch devices

## Accessibility (a11y)

### Minimum Requirements

1. **Keyboard navigation:** Tab through all interactive elements
2. **Screen readers:** Semantic HTML + ARIA labels where needed
3. **Color contrast:** 4.5:1 for text, 3:1 for UI elements
4. **Touch targets:** Minimum 44x44px
5. **Motion:** Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`

```tsx
// ✅ Accessible icon button
<Button size="icon" aria-label="Close dialog">
  <X className="h-4 w-4" />
</Button>

// ✅ Reduced motion support
<div className="motion-safe:animate-fade-in">
  Content
</div>
```

### Focus Management

- Modal opens → focus first focusable element inside
- Modal closes → return focus to trigger element
- Page navigation → focus main content area
- Form error → focus first invalid field

## Anti-Patterns to Avoid

| ❌ Don't | ✅ Do Instead |
|----------|---------------|
| Center everything | Left-align body text and forms |
| Use pure black (#000) | Use dark gray (#111, #1a1a1a) |
| Walls of text | Break into scannable chunks |
| Multiple primary buttons | One clear primary action |
| Tiny click targets | 44px minimum touch targets |
| Surprise modals/popups | User-initiated dialogs only |
| Auto-playing media | Let users control media |
| Infinite scroll everywhere | Pagination for findable content |
| Custom scrollbars | Native scrollbars (except rare cases) |
| Tooltip for essential info | Visible labels and descriptions |

## Design System Consistency

### Maintain Consistency

- Same border-radius everywhere (8px)
- Same shadow scale (sm, md, lg)
- Same animation timings (150ms, 300ms)
- Same spacing scale (4, 8, 12, 16, 24, 32...)
- Same icon style (outline OR filled, not mixed)

### Component Audit Checklist

Before shipping a new component:
- [ ] **Mobile-first:** Works well at 320px width
- [ ] **Touch targets:** Minimum 44x44px tap areas
- [ ] **Thumb-friendly:** Primary actions reachable with one hand
- [ ] Has hover, focus, active states
- [ ] Has loading state (if async)
- [ ] Has error state (if can fail)
- [ ] Has empty state (if can be empty)
- [ ] Has disabled state (if can be disabled)
- [ ] Works with keyboard only
- [ ] Has sufficient color contrast
- [ ] Tested on real mobile device
